cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the design and performance of a cellular technology (NB-IoT) for IoT devices. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper presents mathematical analysis of the time/frequency structure of signals to enhance receiver performance. 
- cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) is another possible category as the paper discusses the coexistence of NB-IoT with legacy LTE systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper addresses implementation details and proposed enhancements to NB-IoT. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also a less likely category but possible as the paper mentions implementation on a commercially deployed Qualcomm FSM platform.
